@NODE install "Installation"
@{u}Installation@{uu}

   Simply copy the entire KewlStory directory to Doors: or unarchive the
KewlStory archive to Doors: and you have it now installed :).

To get it on to the BBS, run it as a standard door, e.g.

 Key:  Function:   Extra:   Lo acc:  Hi acc:  Filename/Name/Dest/Path:
 
 *     34          0        10000    10000    Doors:KewlStory/KewlStory

Or even in @{b}maindoor.text@{ub} if you feeling really adventureous!

   Well, thats it installed really, you can configure the @{b}Menu.text@{ub} to make
it fit in with the rest of your BBS - but I would prefer if you left my BBS
advert in there.. Please! Once the story has begun, you will see a file named
'Text' appear in the KewlStory directory, this file contains the story which
is added to by KewlStory - you may edit this with an ANSI editor, ie. if you
want to take out bits of the story.

   To restart the story, delete the file called @{b}Text@{ub} in the KewlStory
directory, it's that simple :). Now see it @{" in use " LINK use}!

@ENDNODE


@NODE use "In use"
@{u}In use@{uu}

   Once you have @{" installed " LINK install} the door, it's time to check it out,
run it and you will be presented with a menu (@{b}Menu.text@{ub}), you've got an amazing
3 options... Add to story... Read story... and Quit.

   I'm sure you can guess everything, the only special bit of the door is the
editor that allows you to add to the story. This is pretty straight forward and
everything is explained on the screen!

   I'm sorry if it's too easy to understand for you tech-heads, thats about all
the features I could think of tho! Oh, this new version works on MultiNode
systems too!

@ENDNODE


